{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "ZeoliteMadhuri et al. [88] found that up to 30% zeolite improves resistance to chloride and sulfate attacks by 20-30%, enhancing concrete's performance in harsh environments.",
    "Tran et al. [90] reported a 15% increase in sulfate resistance and an 18% reduction in chloride ion penetration, which helps protect concrete from corrosion.",
    "Samimi et al. [91] observed a 12% increase in sulfate resistance and improved acid resistance at a 10% replacement level.",
    "Malolepszy et al. [89] confirmed a 15-20% decrease in susceptibility to sulfate and acid attacks, extending concrete's service life.",
    "Jokar et al. [92] also found improved resistance to chloride and sulfate and a 12-15% reduction in water absorption."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
